Visiting artist studios and checking out art magazines and blog will help collectors get a sense of what you like.

It's not that it's not art. It's just that your money could go further. You could pay something more valuable. - Wimberly
The work that people buy at IKEA, is that art?
"I collect a lot of photography by women". (Two thirds of Pat's collection of 300 works)
The key is does the art enhance your life. That is more important than the price. - Pat Bell
Artists who are represented by galleries have more guidance on what their prices should be.
Pertaining more so to emerging artists the answer: what are you willing to pay? You either buy it or you don't buy it.
How do we understand the value?
A lot of people are interested in who's hot. I'm interested in seeing and discovering new things. -Dexter Wimberly
How do you select the art you buy? "I look for truth and beauty in art." Pat Bell
Patricia Bell has been collecting art since 1989. "I wanted to buy art by artists of today."
